The paper deals with the recognition problem for point visibility graphs, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the existential theory of the reals and the analysis of polynomial inequalities, which are topics in computational complexity theory, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves the study of graphs, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of substructures and universality constructions, which are topics in mathematical logic, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible sub-category.
